title: 17-year-old killed in north Jackson shooting identified
content:
JACKSON, MS (Mississippi News Now) -
One person is dead in a double shooting that happened on Deerfield Lane and Concord Drive.
Seventeen-year-old Jaquez Ingram was shot in the chest and pronounced dead at St. Dominic's Hospital.
The other victim, 20-year-old Malik McIntee, is in stable condition at UMMC, after driving himself to a nearby fire station.
Jackson Police Commander Tyree Jones says there is no active suspect information at this time.
If anyone has any information on this homicide, please contact JPD.
